  "title": "Mechanical Engineer (M&E Contractor)",
  "description": "<ul><li>Support, manage and coordinate Mechanical works and services for building construction projects </li><li>Plan, develop, and manage work schedules to ensure tasks are completed on time.</li><li>Prepare progress reports for clients and project managers, detailing delays, defects, and necessary rectification measures for Mechanical works.</li><li>Provide technical guidance and resolve Mechanical-related issues efficiently.</li><li>Report on Mechanical progress and arrange site inspections with contractors, subcontractors, and clerk-of-works.</li></ul><p>Requirements</p><ul><li>Minimum 1-3 years of relevant experience with an M&E Contractor</li><li>Diploma/Degree in Mechanical, Mechatronics or relevant engineering discipline</li><li>Local construction knowledge</li></ul><p>If the role resonates with you and your professional experience complements the responsibilities listed, send your resume to <strong>koh.dickson@bayesrecruitment.com</strong></p><p>Dickson KOH, EA Registration R1103367</p><p>www.bayesrecruitment.com</p>",
